Converted file pathspec handling to use bash arrays.

Problem: Shellcheck warned about treating array values as strings when accessing
$files after shift/getopts. This can lose array elements and behave unexpectedly
with multiple arguments.

Solution: Converted to proper bash array syntax:
- Changed files=... to files=(...)
- Updated all references to use "${files[@]}" expansion
- Updated empty check to use [[ -z "${files[0]}" ]]

This properly handles multiple file arguments and follows bash best practices for
array handling, ensuring all pathspec arguments are preserved correctly.

/Claude-haiku@4.5
